docs.abstract: Facebook and the agency have been in negotiations over a financial penalty for claims that the company violated a 2011 consent decree.
docs.snippet: Facebook and the agency have been in negotiations over a financial penalty for claims that the company violated a 2011 consent decree.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook said on Wednesday that it expected to be fined up to $5 billion by the Federal Trade Commission for privacy violations. The penalty would be a record by the agency against a technology company and a sign that the United States was willing to punish big tech companies.

headline.main: Facebook Expects to Be Fined Up to $5 Billion by F.T.C. Over Privacy Issues
headline.print_headline: Facebook Says U.S. Regulators Will Hit It Hard
